            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@itsveganjim\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>itsveganjim</span></a></span><br>So all the climate scientists  banging on about stopping the burning  of   fossil fuels are wrong ?</p><p>Lots of billionaires are apparently vegans, their emissons are the size of small nations but a poor farmer in  Cambodia having chicken with his noodles and vegetables is the real problem ?</p><p>----</p><p><a href=\"https://skepticalscience.com/animal-agriculture-meat-global-warming.htm\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" translate=\"no\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"invisible\">https://</span><span class=\"ellipsis\">skepticalscience.com/animal-ag</span><span class=\"invisible\">riculture-meat-global-warming.htm</span></a></p><p>&gt;The burning of fossil fuels for electricity and heat accounts for the majority of greenhouse gas emissions, totaling 31% of annual global greenhouse gas emissions, followed by transportation at 15%, manufacturing at 12.4% and animal agriculture at 11%</p>",
